24/03/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) emerged as the leader in the latest opinion poll conducted by ANAR. The results, published on Tuesday (23 March), show AKP receiving 46.2 per cent of voter support, followed by the main opposition Republican People's Party, with 20.2 per cent, and the Nationalist Movement Party, with 7.2 per cent. The survey also found that AKP could win 49.3 per cent and 42 per cent of the votes in Ankara and Istanbul respectively in Sunday's local elections. (Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News, NTV - 23/03/04)
